<h2>Common Railroad Encroachment Issues</h2>
<p>Table 1 lists common encroachment issues faced by freight rail transportation.  One obvious source of conflict between railroad activity and other uses occurs at grade crossings, where long, slow trains impede the flow of vehicle traffic (including emergency vehicles).  Less obvious conflicts include the noise and vibration caused by freight trains that are not only nuisances but, particularly in the case of vibration, can also cause physical damage.</p>  
 
